<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="879" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d879">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/2195</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Denby</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-26"><hi rend="italic">January 26,
                                1922</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In compliance with the request in your
                            letter of January 24, 1922, LA 837.00/2184, orders will be immediately
                            issued directing the withdrawal of the Marine Corps garrison now at
                            Camaguey, Cuba.</p>
                        <p>This detachment will be withdrawn to the U.S. Naval Station, Guantanamo
                            Bay, Cuba, where it will complete its target practice and whence it will
                            be returned North on vessels of the Fleet early next spring.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin Denby</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>